      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a451ff53ef76.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3e0de8e6bf2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3e0e0ec3bcb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Allows the Master Sword to be displayed in Link's House. The only way I could find to do this was to set &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;IsMasterSword&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;to false, which has some... interesting side effects.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Side Effects:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Master Sword beams had to be disabled(see video)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Trial of the Sword damage progression no longer applies (I included options so you can manually adjust the damage to match your progression)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Master Sword will break fully, like any other weapon(unbreakable option is available if you don't want to do durability transfer or anything)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Master Sword no longer enters awakened state, neither from malice or trial of the sword&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;</description>
